DE_DELTAMILL2

Created by: Wheel-Knee
Contact: wheelknee@gmail.com
Release Date: March 25/2005
Capacity: 32 vs. 32 (64)
Works with Bots: Yes - Optimized .nav file by Effexx at www.punkassfraggers.com

OBJECTIVE

Terrorist's must bomb the mill stockpiles, or the dam to disable food production.
CT's must protect their mill, and foodstocks for Delta.

This map is based on an Old Stone Mill built in 1810 in Delta Ontario. It was build by a loyalist and industrialist from Vermont. This mill is one of the oldest surviving mills in Ontario and is a example of early Canadian Architecture, and pioneer industrial development.

Enjoy
Wheel-Knee

This map is like a futuristic community. It is a small section of a huge city that uses an irrigation system to supply each section with water. This section just happens to be on the delta of the river, thus the name.

This is a small defusion map set in a sewer. I wanted to make a map with quick action and a sense of claustrophobia. There are gloomy areas and industrial areas, and some piping. This is my second real Source map, so I was trying to master indoor areas.

There are two bomb sites and three mixers, with good flow and variation in combat distance. If you see any bugs, feel free to let me know. Thanks and have fun.

A remake of my original map to a more familar objective.  Objective is to bomb the underground dungeon destroying the "pets" or to destroy the castle via the third story.  Watch out as there are many traps all triggered by pressure pads.

This is a beta so please let me know of problems.  Some things might have not made the transfer from the DM style to DE so please let me know.  Also there are a lot of breakable areas, chances are if you run into a dead end its breakable.  The dungeon itself is only accesible by breaking one of three entrances.

2 big questions I have are:  I left a "jail" from the deathmatch version that is currently unaccesible in any way other than noclip.  If you would like go below the map and into the two story room.  Up above is a iron pillar/button that will release some "pets" on unsuspecting players below.  let me know if I should incorporate this into the DE style.  Should the wall towers stay the way they are or should I make them square.

Also planning on try to make it work for hostages so if you like this it might be something to look forward to.  If you would like to try it on my server or want a personal tour you can try to find me here 8.12.20.203:27015

Please try and comment!

**Updated:  Things have taken more a fantasy turn though I'm not sure I like it
New breakable lights
New bombzone B layout
Another passage to get to bombzone B

I have also included a seperate map file with orange textures or pillars pointing out some of the secrets.  The orange textures can be found in de_defendthecastle_explanation

So I finally got around to editing and revising this map.  Has some nice new editions, better quality textures, nice lighting.

Suitable for snipers, rogues (rushers), team play, and even fun against bots for home or lan users!
Enjoy!

This map was created originally as a part of the 2007 Joe.to Halloween Map Pack:
http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/36702

It was an honor to be a part of this map-pack again this year! Last year, my submission for the map-pack was a map called de_nightmare. It was rather well-received, so I wanted to be certain that I did a better job on this one.

This is somewhat of a re-visioning of de_nightmare, using some ideas that I originally wanted to use for cs_nightmare, but I scrapped that map in favor of this one. This map makes use of some randomly selected "events" that are set to occur every round. Each round should be a surprise, and hopefully this will catch people off-guard.

Also, I have heard that this map may cause server crashes when there are 20 or more people in the server. If you receive ANY major server crashes, I would really like to know. Thanks.

There's much more information in the actual readme file, so enjoy!

de_daybreak complete w/ HDR

following my HL2DM map I decided to make a CSS map. This map is called de_daybreak, a fuse between cs_office and de_nuke. Terrorists spawn with their APC's outside the building. Their main objective is to either destroy the generator room which supplies power, or blow up the office in the heart of the building. CT's were air dropped and spawn on a helipad ont the roof. The map layout is built so the CT's have many way to defend both bomb sites, while the T's have many ways to infiltrate each. It is a defend and assault map, and has HDR enabled.

This map also has some custom models, decals, and textures.

-Spas12

Terrorists:

Your organization has aquired the computer software that is worth millions
to the wealthy client that hired you. Now the client is refusing to pay you
for the software untill you destroy the only other copy that is stored on
the server at the original programmers work location.
You have discovered that their are two ways you can achieve this task.
1: Destroy the main server using C4 explosives.
2: Destroy the Electrical Sub station causing a power surge to corrupt all 
   data stored on the servers.



Counter Terrorists:

You have been watching the activities of a wealthy business man suspected
of industrial espionage for 8 months. You have learnt from a reliable
informant inside his organization that he has been using a terrorist faction
to steal and destroy software developed by other companies.
In a follow up investigation into this information you have discovered that
the terrorists are planing to destroy data stored at a computer programing
company. This is the break you have been waiting for.
Intercept the terrorists before they can destroy the data using whatever
force is necessary and gather evidence to convict the business man.

This is one of my first maps. I made it because I wanted a map where people had to use cunning and the only way that would happen is if people couldn't see a damn thing. Pretty much all the map is pitch black beside the spawn (so you can see t get into the play area) and the bomb site, which causes a dilemma for the T's. Do they risk certain death to win the round or do they hang back and hope to kill all the enemies.

Anyways this is an amazingly small map which could make it quite hectic in the dark.

PO, y'all.
